This sample shows how to read all SCVars UserVars and print them to the Console.

var scVars = Prime.Services.UserVarService.GetAllNamesFromCollection("SCVars");
foreach (var userVar in scVars)
{
    var userVarValue = Prime.Services.UserVarService.GetStringValue("SCVars", userVar);
    Prime.Services.ConsoleService.PrintDebug(() => $"SC UserVar[{userVar}]=[{userVarValue}]", sessionContext);
}

This sample shows how to read all collection names and print them to console.

var collections = Prime.Services.UserVarService.GetAllCollections();
foreach (var collection in collections)
{
    Prime.Services.ConsoleService.PrintDebug(() => $"Collection name=[{collection}]", sessionContext);
}

This shows how to get if an userVar exists in  SCVars.

if (Prime.Services.UserVarService.ExistsInScVarsCollection("mySCVarName")){
    DoSomenthingElse();
}

